" ================================
" Task: Change User Details
" Why: Role or team change
" ================================

" 1. Change the login shell for a user
" Explanation: If the user switches role, they might need a different shell.
" Option 1: Using usermod
sudo usermod -s /bin/bash username
" -s specifies the new login shell

" Option 2: Using chsh
sudo chsh -s /bin/bash username
" chsh also changes the user's login shell

" 2. Change the home directory for a user
" Explanation: When a user's home directory needs to be updated (e.g., for a new project or role).
sudo usermod -d /new/home/directory -m username
" -d specifies the new home directory
" -m moves the existing contents to the new directory

" 3. Change the primary group of a user
" Explanation: Useful when a user moves to a different team or group.
sudo usermod -g newgroup username
" -g sets the new primary group for the user

"4. Check the user's primary group
id username
" The 'gid' field shows the primary group

"5. Verification / Checking the changes
" Check all details of the user
getent passwd username
" Shows: username, UID, GID, home directory, shell, etc.
